# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Chatbot
#
# A provider is three strings: where, who, what. That is the whole abstraction -
# swapping Gemini for OpenRouter, or either for a paid model, is an edit to this
# file and nothing else. See docs/adr/0002 and docs/chatbot.md.
#
# Both providers below speak the OpenAI wire format, which is why one client can
# talk to either. Google's OpenAI-compatible layer is officially beta and will
# *silently ignore* parameters it does not recognise - if a setting seems to do
# nothing, that is why.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Primary: Gemini free tier (15 req/min, 1,000 req/day at time of writing).
# Key from https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# Confirm the current model id in AI Studio - Google renames these often, and a
# stale id is a 404 at request time, not at build time.
CHAT_PRIMARY_BASE_URL="https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai/"
CHAT_PRIMARY_API_KEY=""
CHAT_PRIMARY_MODEL="gemini-flash-lite-latest"

# Fallback: OpenRouter. Optional - leave blank and the chain is simply shorter.
# This rescues a provider *outage*. It barely touches a provider *quota*: the
# free tier here is 50 req/day against Gemini's 1,000, so it adds roughly 5%
# headroom. It is the seatbelt, not the brakes. The brakes are the WAF rule.
CHAT_FALLBACK_BASE_URL="https://openrouter.ai/api/v1"
CHAT_FALLBACK_API_KEY=""
CHAT_FALLBACK_MODEL=""

# The circuit-breaker: model calls per day before the bot starts handing off.
# Keep it below the provider's own ceiling, so running out is a decision we made
# rather than a 429 a recruiter discovered.
CHAT_DAILY_BUDGET="800"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Upstash Redis - the circuit-breaker and the Question Log.
#
# Optional. With these unset, the bot still works: the breaker fails open and
# nothing is logged. A cache outage must never take down the thing a recruiter
# came to use. See docs/adr/0003 and docs/adr/0004.
#
# Provision from the Vercel dashboard (Storage -> Upstash); it injects these
# two variables automatically.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=""
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=""
